T1  - Who Writes the News? Corporate Press Releases during Merger Negotiations
AU  - AHERN, KENNETH R.
AU  - SOSYURA, DENIS
Y1  - 2014/02/01
PY  - 2014
DA  - 2014/02/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/jofi.12109
T2  - The Journal of Finance
JF  - The Journal of Finance
JO  - The Journal of Finance
JA  - The Journal of Finance
SP  - 241
EP  - 291
VL  - 69
IS  - 1
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0022-1082
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/jofi.12109
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - ABSTRACT Firms have an incentive to manage media coverage to influence their stock prices during important corporate events. Using comprehensive data on media coverage and merger negotiations, we find that bidders in stock mergers originate substantially more news stories after the start of merger negotiations, but before the public announcement. This strategy generates a short-lived run-up in bidders' stock prices during the period when the stock exchange ratio is determined, which substantially impacts the takeover price. Our results demonstrate that the timing and content of financial media coverage may be biased by firms seeking to manipulate their stock price.
ER  - 

