T1  - An Anatomy of Commodity Futures Risk Premia
AU  - SZYMANOWSKA, MARTA
AU  - DE ROON, FRANS
AU  - NIJMAN, THEO
AU  - VAN DEN GOORBERGH, ROB
Y1  - 2014/02/01
PY  - 2014
DA  - 2014/02/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/jofi.12096
T2  - The Journal of Finance
JF  - The Journal of Finance
JO  - The Journal of Finance
JA  - The Journal of Finance
SP  - 453
EP  - 482
VL  - 69
IS  - 1
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0022-1082
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/jofi.12096
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - ABSTRACT We identify two types of risk premia in commodity futures returns: spot premia related to the risk in the underlying commodity, and term premia related to changes in the basis. Sorting on forecasting variables such as the futures basis, return momentum, volatility, inflation, hedging pressure, and liquidity results in sizable spot premia between 5% and 14% per annum and term premia between 1% and 3% per annum. We show that a single factor, the high-minus-low portfolio from basis sorts, explains the cross-section of spot premia. Two additional basis factors are needed to explain the term premia.
